# Shader & R3F conventions

## Where shader code lives

- Co-locate shaders next to their consuming component:
  ```
  components/Methodology.tsx
  components/methodology/
    voxelIllustrativeShader.ts   ← exports vert/frag strings
    abstractFormArchive.ts       ← scratch / archived formulas
  ```
- Export pairs as `*_VERT` / `*_FRAG` constants tagged `/* glsl */` for editor highlighting.

## Uniform naming

- `u_time`, `u_progress` (0..1 scroll), `u_step` (state index), `u_mouse3D`, `u_resolution`.
- Shock / ripple events: `u_shockTime`, `u_shockOrigin` — single shock per frame, fired by setting `shockRef.current = true`.

## Mandatory helpers in vertex shaders

```glsl
vec3 safeNorm(vec3 p) {
  float l = length(p);
  if (l < 1e-5) return vec3(0.0, 1.0, 0.0);
  return p / l;
}
```

Always guard `acos`, `normalize`, divisions when the input can be near zero.

## TSL / WebGPU migration (target for Vague 5)

When porting a GLSL pair to TSL:

1. Keep the GLSL source in the same file under a `_LEGACY` constant for diff/review.
2. Build the TSL graph as a function `buildXxxMaterial({ progress, time, mouse, … })` returning a `THREE.NodeMaterial`.
3. Detect WebGPU support at canvas init; fall back to GLSL automatically.

## R3F materials

- Memoize material/geometry with `useMemo` (prevents reupload on re-render).
- Dispose in the matching `useEffect` cleanup — both `geometry.dispose()` and `material.dispose()`.
- For instanced geometries, also dispose the source `EdgesGeometry` and any `InstancedBufferGeometry`.

## Blob / SDF style

For organic squircles use the existing super-ellipse pattern (`x^n + y^n = 1`, `n = SUPER_N = 4`) — see `ProjectGrid.tsx`. Don't reinvent.
